pr_title: Milestone 1.1 (Helping learners when they get Stuck): State migration for the field `dest_if_really_stuck`
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of #[fill_in_number_here].
2. This PR does the following: Adds the dest_if_really_stuck field to the Outcome class and in another derived field default_outcome. This field would help in creation of an alternate dest to direct the learners to, if they are really stuck.

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.


-->

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76519771/177944292-154e496b-842b-4144-bcea-f74789a04894.mp4


Steps followed: 
1. Started dev server in develop using flag  --save_datastore
2. Created a new exploration on develop, and saved it.
3. Downloaded the YAML, no dest_if_stuck field existed.
4. Stopped the server.
5. Checkout to migration branch, and start dev server using same flag.
6. Opened the previously created new exploration.
7. New field exists in the updated YAML file.


#### Proof of changes on desktop with slow/throttled network
Not required since no frontend changes are made, only a new field is added to Outcome and DefaultOutcome
<!--
Make sure to properly verify that everything works correctly, and that there are
no weird UI mistakes or other problems. Also, if there are any newly added fields,
try to fill them out and test that different inputs are correctly accepted/rejected.

Throttle the network (to 3G) using the browser Developer Tools (see references below).
There should be no performance or UI issues while the network is slow.

References:
 - Chrome: https://css-tricks.com/throttling-the-network/
 - Firefox: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Network_Monitor/Throttling
-->

#### Proof of changes on mobile phone

<!--
In some cases this is not needed (e.g. for pages that we do not expect to
support mobile phones, or for backend-only features).

Feel free to use the Developer Tools emulator for this.

References:
 - Chrome: https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/device-mode/
 - Firefox: https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/devtools-user/index.html#responsive-design-mode
-->

#### Proof of changes in Arabic language

<!--
If the PR changes the UI in any of the files listed in rtl_css.py (i.e, those that have
a separate .rtl.css file for styling), make sure to add screenshots with the site
language set to Arabic as well (we use Arabic as it is a language written from right to left).
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

E.g.:

- The dest_if_really_stuck should actually be a valid state name.
- If the answer group is marked as "correct" then there shouldn't be a dest_if_really_stuck
- The dest_if_really_stuck shouldn't match the name of the state it is currently being used for
- When checking that every state is reachable from the start, you'd need to consider the dest_if_really_stuck links as well (this is in addition to what I imagine are existing checks to ensure that, with only the regular dest links, every state can reach the end).

I might have missed some, so please think through the different cases and ensure there are tests for these. Better to make this robust now so that you don't get people creating invalid explorations which we need to clean up later.

/cc @iamprayush ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 9, 4, 40, 31, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'seanlip', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917227015, 'comment_body': "Right, all the arguments make sense. Actually:

- A regex check would ensure that the state name entered is a valid one. Also, since the creator chooses the dest_if_really_stuck state from a dropdown or creates a new one, only valid states will be assigned to this field.
- In M1.2, a check is added that the dest_if_really_stuck UI become visible only if the answer group is not marked as correct.
- The same state name wouldn't appear in the dropdown. So, the case of a self-loop would be checked in the frontend itself.
- Actually, the check for this can only be implemented in M1.3 when new types of links would be created to connect the dest_if_really_stuck state.

Basically, these conditions will be applied in the frontend itself.
PS: I'll push the backend tests for the validation soon.
", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 9, 6, 1, 11, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Manan-Rathi', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 917227437, 'comment_body': "Note that all the validation checks have to be complete in the backend though. pr_title: Milestone 1.2 & Milestone 1.3 (Helping learners when they get stuck): Add the frontend changes for the new dest_if_really_stuck component and create new dotted links.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

**NOTE:** This is a PR based on #15644 and has changes inherited from it. So, please review from [here](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/pull/15698/files/f79428fa2d2df3b8c34af1045679002ab738ecb9..333dd622b7e8e84fab2cf62bc69e2c3821b9379e)

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of #[fill_in_number_here].
2. This PR does the following:

- Add UI component for new field.
- Make necessary changes to store and emit data.
- Add an info-tooltip for the new component.
- Added a flag to turn on-off the feature (destIfStuckFeatEnabled)
- The new dest_if_really_stuck state is connected to the others via a dotted line.

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.
-->


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76519771/185103810-d9359d27-953c-4e7b-bb49-e91743c3e598.mp4






#### Proof of changes on desktop with slow/throttled network

<!--
Make sure to properly verify that everything works correctly, and that there are
no weird UI mistakes or other problems. Also, if there are any newly added fields,
try to fill them out and test that different inputs are correctly accepted/rejected.

Throttle the network (to 3G) using the browser Developer Tools (see references below).
There should be no performance or UI issues while the network is slow.

References:
 - Chrome: https://css-tricks.com/throttling-the-network/
 - Firefox: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Network_Monitor/Throttling
-->


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76519771/185103886-623a31b0-ca63-4c9b-b2f6-ffc56dab627a.mp4




#### Proof of changes on mobile phone

<!--
In some cases this is not needed (e.g. for pages that we do not expect to
support mobile phones, or for backend-only features).

Feel free to use the Developer Tools emulator for this.

References:
 - Chrome: https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/device-mode/
 - Firefox: https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/devtools-user/index.html#responsive-design-mode
-->

#### Proof of changes in Arabic language

<!--
If the PR changes the UI in any of the files listed in rtl_css.py (i.e, those that have
a separate .rtl.css file for styling), make sure to add screenshots with the site
language set to Arabic as well (we use Arabic as it is a language written from right to left).
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

pr_title: M2.1 (Helping learners when they get stuck): Add state migration for new customization_arg catchMisspellings.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of NA.
2. This PR does the following: Adds a new customization_arg (catchMisspellings) to TextInput interaction.
The new catchMisspellings customization_arg will allow the creators to detect if the learner has misspelled the answer (Checked by detecting an edit distance of atmost 2), and accordingly give a more meaningful response. For eg: Instead of responding with "The answer is incorrect", the response would now be - "Could you please check the spelling?".

pr_title: M2.2 & M2.3 (Helping learners when they get stuck): Add functions to detect misspellings and render meaningful responses.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of NA
2. This PR does the following:
- Detect answers misspelled by at most 2 characters and render a meaningful Oppia response from a set of predetermined responses.

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [ ] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.
-->

#### Proof of changes on desktop with slow/throttled network

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76519771/196030772-565d096d-a1cf-42f3-b6cd-73c8501aea71.mp4




<!--
Make sure to properly verify that everything works correctly, and that there are
no weird UI mistakes or other problems. Also, if there are any newly added fields,
try to fill them out and test that different inputs are correctly accepted/rejected.

Throttle the network (to 3G) using the browser Developer Tools (see references below).
There should be no performance or UI issues while the network is slow.

References:
 - Chrome: https://css-tricks.com/throttling-the-network/
 - Firefox: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Network_Monitor/Throttling
-->

#### Proof of changes on mobile phone

<!--
In some cases this is not needed (e.g. for pages that we do not expect to
support mobile phones, or for backend-only features).

Feel free to use the Developer Tools emulator for this.

References:
 - Chrome: https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/device-mode/
 - Firefox: https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/devtools-user/index.html#responsive-design-mode
-->

#### Proof of changes in Arabic language

<!--
If the PR changes the UI, make sure to add screenshots with the site
language set to Arabic as well (we use Arabic as it is a language written from right to left).
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Make-a-pull-request).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia's-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-CI-checks-fail-on-your-PR).

pr_title: M2.4, 2.5, 2.6 & M2.7 (Helping learners when they get stuck): Add support to detect a stuck learner and provide appropriate assistance.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of NA.
2. This PR does the following: Add support to detect a stuck learner and provide the predetermined, appropriate [assistance flow](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1kpR07JFL86XecLzzQXBGTVmyvWNQ4ymsiGfE96stqEs/edit#bookmark=id.shbrywmumtm8).


## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.
-->

#### Proof of changes on desktop with slow/throttled network

<!--
Make sure to properly verify that everything works correctly, and that there are
no weird UI mistakes or other problems. Also, if there are any newly added fields,
try to fill them out and test that different inputs are correctly accepted/rejected.

Throttle the network (to 3G) using the browser Developer Tools (see references below).
There should be no performance or UI issues while the network is slow.

References:
 - Chrome: https://css-tricks.com/throttling-the-network/
 - Firefox: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Network_Monitor/Throttling
-->
##### Case when only hints and solution exists
##### What happens:
In 1st half:
- Hints are used up.
- Solution is released _if it exists_ when the learner gets stuck after the threshold time limit is reached.

In 2nd half:
- Hints are used up.
- Solution is released _if it exists_ when the learner submits 3 incorrect answers (Threshold wrong answer limit for judging if the learner is stuck) after consuming the hints.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76519771/198975980-570eb32b-bb5f-4e4b-9b21-59da215d787a.mp4



##### Case when:
- Hints are exhausted.
- Learner has made atleast one incorrect submission.
- Threshold for deciding that the learner is stuck is reached, and a dest_if_really_stuck state exists for the learner to be redirected to for improving the concepts, etc.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76519771/198865744-03626ae6-fb4e-45d9-93d4-418b9f3654a6.mp4




##### Case when:
- Concept card for the state exists.
- The learner submits 3 incorrect answers or crosses the threshold time limit, is now declared stuck, and then redirected to the stuck state if it exists.



https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76519771/198015412-29003796-7613-49f6-bec8-2bb6e1a03d75.mp4

##### Support for Concept card (**New feature**):
- A tooltip and icon appears nudging the learner towards the concept card.
- The learner can click on the card to view the revision contents.


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76519771/198016086-b634a8ce-72e0-4bb8-b494-017234e40bb4.mp4


#### Proof of changes on mobile phone

<!--
In some cases this is not needed (e.g. for pages that we do not expect to
support mobile phones, or for backend-only features).

Feel free to use the Developer Tools emulator for this.

References:
 - Chrome: https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/device-mode/
 - Firefox: https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/devtools-user/index.html#responsive-design-mode
-->

#### Proof of changes in Arabic language

<!--
If the PR changes the UI, make sure to add screenshots with the site
language set to Arabic as well (we use Arabic as it is a language written from right to left).
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Make-a-pull-request).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia's-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-CI-checks-fail-on-your-PR).
